From 250228262ef6befb8f58ef70f6ce61497c8002a7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Wed, 29 Apr 2026 10:32:43 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 076/174] microblaze: align swapper_pg_dir to MMUPAGE_SIZE
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The TLB miss handler in hw_exception_handler.S computes the PGD entry
address with

  or  r4, r4, r5

where r4 is the page-directory base (swapper_pg_dir for kernel maps)
and r5 is the offset of the entry within the directory.  This bitwise-
or is correct only when the base is MMUPAGE-aligned: any low bits set
in r4 collide with the offset and yield a different address.

The original swapper_pg_dir definition relied on incidental .data
alignment.  Pre-PGCL it happened to land on a 4 KiB boundary; with
PGCL changing the data layout (notably the new debug_fault_capture
work and the THREAD_SIZE fix's reshuffling of .data), it ended up at
0xc08c3140 — a 64-byte boundary.  The TLB miss handler then read PGD
entries from the wrong offset, treated random data as PTE pointers,
and the first vmalloc/ioremap mapping (xintc's 0xf0000008) faulted
in `xintc_write` → `_exception` → `die` → panic.

Add an explicit `.balign MMUPAGE_SIZE` so swapper_pg_dir lands on a
4 KiB boundary regardless of preceding .data layout.

Result: microblaze with PAGE_MMUSHIFT=4 now boots end-to-end on
qemu-system-microblaze -M petalogix-s3adsp1800 (big-endian), reaches
"console [ttyUL0] enabled", runs init, and pgcl-test 19/19 +
pgcl-stress 12/12 PASS.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 arch/microblaze/kernel/head.S | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/microblaze/kernel/head.S b/arch/microblaze/kernel/head.S
index e72c6c5ebbb6..8398b40766a3 100644
--- a/arch/microblaze/kernel/head.S
+++ b/arch/microblaze/kernel/head.S
@@ -39,6 +39,12 @@
 #include <asm/processor.h>
 
 .section .data
+# swapper_pg_dir must be MMUPAGE-aligned: the TLB miss handler in
+# hw_exception_handler.S computes the PGD entry address with an
+# "or r4, r4, r5" of pg_dir base and offset, which is correct only
+# when the base is MMUPAGE-aligned so the low offset bits do not
+# collide with the base.
+.balign MMUPAGE_SIZE
 .global swapper_pg_dir
 swapper_pg_dir:
 	.space	MMUPAGE_SIZE
-- 
2.54.0

